321 243 440 (   back_insert_iterator) 440 SB
321 299 446 (   front_insert_iterator) 446 SB
321 355 323 (   insert_iterator) 323 SB
321 411 372 (   ostream_iterator) 372 SB
321 467 904 (   [Note: ostreambuf_iterator is also affected]) 904 SB
321 579 941 (   are all currently specified in the standard as:) 941 SB
321 691 921 (   insert_iterator<Container> operator++\(int\);) 921 SB
321 803 1241 (   I was wondering why the HP implementation has them as:) 1241 SB
321 915 957 (   insert_iterator<Container>& operator++\(int\);) 957 SB
321 1027 1039 (   The reason is that if the user tries something like:) 1039 SB
321 1139 210 (   *i++ = 0;) 210 SB
321 1251 1226 (   where i is an insert_iterator, an insert_iterator<Container>) 1226 SB
321 1307 1060 (   copy ctor would automatically be called under the) 1060 SB
321 1363 1020 (   current specification. I don't think you want this) 1020 SB
321 1419 1149 (   to happen, especially in the HP implementation where) 1149 SB
321 1475 1130 (   the private data members are of type Container& and) 1130 SB
321 1531 424 (   Container::iterator.) 424 SB
321 1643 1138 (   So my proposal is to return by reference in each of the) 1138 SB
321 1699 462 (   postfix ++ operators.) 462 SB
321 1811 1241 (See also issue 32 regarding the return type of insert_iterator::) 1241 SB
321 1867 327 (operator++\(int\).) 327 SB
321 1979 246 ( Discussion:) 246 SB
321 2035 1294 (    In general, the result of operator++\(int\) is a temporary which) 1294 SB
321 2091 1152 (    is needed only for the duration of the expression.  The) 1152 SB
321 2147 1326 (    iterators described in Clause 24 are described uniformly in this) 1326 SB
321 2203 1260 (    regard.  However, the iterators specified in this issue are all) 1260 SB
321 2259 1381 (    output iterators.  For them there is no need to return a temporary) 1381 SB
321 2315 1276 (    \(usually \(*this\) is returned\).  The standard could be changed) 1276 SB
321 2371 784 (    to return a reference for these items.) 784 SB
321 2483 1302 (    The specifications for output iterators \(and input iterators\) do) 1302 SB
321 2539 1254 (    not require the return result for operator++\(int\) to be of the) 1254 SB
321 2595 1284 (    same class.  The specifications are therefore somewhat open-) 1284 SB
321 2651 1292 (    ended.  However, some return value must be specified in the) 1292 SB
321 2707 1159 (    iterators described in this section.  One possibility is to) 1159 SB
321 2763 1315 (    change the return types to references, another is to leave them) 1315 SB
321 2819 1360 (    as they are but provide additional discussion in the introduction) 1360 SB
321 2875 1286 (    stating that any return type which meets the specifications is) 1286 SB
1 #C
